{"title":"- Hemorragia del Intestino Delgado-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Gastroenterología/- Hemorragia del Intestino Delgado-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Hemorragia del\\NIntestino Delgado","guid":"b0qXVmzhgDxXqljEI0MHgQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Introducción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Dificultad en la\\NIdentificación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• Históricamente: Diagnóstico de HD de origen oscuro (HDOO) cuando endoscopia\\Nalta y colonoscopía eran no reveladoras y HD o anemia ferropénica persistían.","guid":"aROAv1ZUPNErcl1LHtd7Vw","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• HDOO: Representa aproximadamente el 5%-10% de todas las HD.","guid":"aUa_8HoLg3UqnoP_QQ_YGA","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Nuevas Tecnologías:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• Cápsula Endoscópica (CE).","guid":"LtBwMXwspjZFlVruFXjpMg","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"• Enteroscopía Profunda Asistida por Dispositivos.","guid":"LR05wm31im1_f-o3GC2psA","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"5","text":"• Técnicas de Radiología: Tomografía computarizada multifase.","guid":"HoVcPzzxgGNwrNYoSytzcA","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"1","text":"• Resultados: Identificación de causa en el 40%-75% de los casos\\Nde HDOO, generalmente en el intestino delgado (ID).","guid":"RrfI-k1DGg4xMt-pTWe_Ng","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"• Terminología Actual:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Sospecha de Hemorragia del\\NIntestino Delgado (HID):","guid":"BozLqldEXloqVaoxdddjAQ","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"• Definición: Sangrado del tracto gastrointestinal (GI) entre la ampolla de Vater y la válvula ileocecal.","guid":"RCXelgIAAvUZGmqCLTlfVQ","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"• Diagnóstico: Endoscopia digestiva alta (EDA), colonoscopía total y, eventualmente, repetidas en caso de duda o sospecha clínica.","guid":"WFQ_xkSMx85MENqtQZr_tg","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"• Guía: Terminología adoptada desde la guía 2015 del American College of Gastroenterology (ACG).","guid":"PphLQ3avXqwCqtfObWi7dA","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"10","text":"• Diferenciación\\Nde HDOO:","guid":"ctwE4khAMr0C4aSmH_k-pA","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• HDOO: Reservado para casos con origen desconocido\\Nluego de un estudio completo de ID negativo.","guid":"NjW9KgJhjt04JuhUVLsZaQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"1","text":"• Clasificación de HID:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Evidente o Manifiesta: Sangrado visible (hematoquecia o melena).","guid":"P1MPQSjTvn0f5ozaBgrYOw","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Oculta: Sangrado no visible, basado en test de sangre oculta en\\Ndeposiciones positivo, con o sin anemia ferropénica.","guid":"dhbYi1EZbINTcpdxfKOkNQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"0","text":"Etiología","guid":"KF3K3n3IQaJyewc2bIOpdA","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• Edad de presentación:","guid":"AWZzwid5bf5vk2U0QLmDAw","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• < 40 años:","guid":"f8hEmAuVcbkZvQjKWByEXg","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal (enfermedad de Crohn de ID).","guid":"UCI5h2XN43cZt4QVDrqEyg","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"• Lesiones vasculares (angiodisplasias, Dieulafoy, erosiones, úlceras inducidas por AINEs).","guid":"XH1CIxxiW-N8I0A-T1lHBQ","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"22","text":"• Tumores de ID (linfoma, tumores estromales (GIST), neuroendocrinos, adenocarcinomas, metástasis).","guid":"ZKKOoH8E5OVvUoWqGthLyg","children":[]}]},{"id":"26","parent":"21","text":"• > 40 años:","guid":"UE0sew958g5GxFs-RmQFBg","children":[{"id":"27","parent":"26","text":"• Lesiones vasculares (angiodisplasias, Dieulafoy, erosiones, úlceras inducidas por AINEs).","guid":"YJNekRo28q9DB6k8CPEpbw","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"26","text":"• Tumores de ID (linfoma, tumores estromales (GIST), neuroendocrinos, adenocarcinomas, metástasis).","guid":"F_80UjWCsHJ1dNLkF8d46g","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"26","text":"• Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal (enfermedad de Crohn de ID).","guid":"QRgiKw8x265v4_1IETpbsg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"20","text":"Otras Causas\\NInfrecuentes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"• Enteropatía por radiación.","guid":"Jf3dQRwYILsg1khNCqBr4Q","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"• Enteropatía portal hipertensiva.","guid":"Gx0FoBAozfcleLesHIN5Yg","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"• Várices ectópicas.","guid":"N6I79hUMHOBdPPxmB-9ocQ","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"• Origen\\Nextraluminal:","guid":"ErFFgV3i9NgZMEUEB7EEpg","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"• Hemosuccus pancreaticus.","guid":"JIYO7iQBV6ROU214BRltfw","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"• Hemobilia.","guid":"PjhKVBFbFrQOCpbvVjd-pg","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"• Fístulas aorto-entéricas.","guid":"Rt3HJgN_adNt_veQB_XpUg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"UqGT5GoawaRJvsCadyei0g","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"• Anamnesis:","guid":"CXC8_wQi1-hC5WMhFzvOEw","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"• Edad y forma de presentación: Hematemesis, hematoquecia, melena.","guid":"DhwZSRgSLhJ8QRBSTFRjnQ","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"• Síntomas adicionales: Pérdida de peso, obstrucción intestinal.","guid":"KW1ExgpLp0Eii-JDcEsL7Q","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"39","text":"• Comorbilidades: Cardiovasculares, enfermedad cardíaca valvular, daño hepático crónico, coagulopatías.","guid":"DcsRFBCK2dN4QPU_IHxWlQ","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"39","text":"• Medicamentos: AINEs, aspirina, antitrombóticos.","guid":"bm3OqxFxOkMoLVs7VexE4Q","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"39","text":"• Radioterapia.","guid":"SpZfxAFbYSljaJhYH9OmAA","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"39","text":"• Antecedentes de cáncer.","guid":"e1-vZHuFV7EQLfHcBYzLlw","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"39","text":"• Cirugías previas: Trasplante hepático, reparación de aneurisma aórtico abdominal, resección intestinal.","guid":"ORrOtR0LtxtHXCPAC7ximg","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"39","text":"• Antecedentes familiares: Poliposis familiar, enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal.","guid":"ByZ4vxEa5FsC5AVsFUKSCA","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"38","text":"• Examen físico:","guid":"OqRkJH-w7A4ApEwoY9F2kQ","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"• Lesiones oculares y orales.","guid":"KS0SbX8lFb5hlvWlUppXNA","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"• Telangiectasias.","guid":"FK2xuzsmWGA3uCSoAxuAZw","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"• Masas abdominales.","guid":"TJeSo1_lf-NZB8VIFy3yaA","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"• Dermatitis herpetiforme.","guid":"YUDhDDxwXaE3AZhoXKCQcQ","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"48","text":"• Eritema nodoso.","guid":"N_W1UkcvikViLVwIcRCEBw","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"48","text":"• Estado nutricional.","guid":"ZDtBYCmJf8l8zOaha2G6Hw","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"38","text":"Métodos de\\NDiagnóstico","guid":"SOq6dFWaJzVAQDtjL0jUKg","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"1. Repetir estudios endoscópicos\\Nconvencionales (“segunda mirada”):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• Justificación:","guid":"Zl4ZtnlRMOYfgozfewvLcQ","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"• Hasta 25% de los casos, la causa está al alcance del estudio endoscópico convencional.","guid":"NHeJRlc6sYh-J0vYAQ8b6g","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"• Lesiones de Cameron, GAVE, divertículos, pólipos de colon.","guid":"NyAxa1cvESEYPQ5SGGESeA","children":[]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"• Recomendaciones:","guid":"E59uwk8-prp1AaLpS5UkFA","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"• Repetir EDA si hay antecedentes de hematemesis, melena, o examen previamente no completo/poco satisfactorio.","guid":"Fm4w_1cu_vE8pagbeqlyXw","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"• Repetir colonoscopía total en casos de hematoquecia recurrente o sospecha de origen bajo del sangrado.","guid":"ALh-ujlyjr1mCyx_O1zi3g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"55","text":"Cápsula Endoscópica (CE)","guid":"f6r8lRyvC54Gfr2uE0prVw","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"• Examen de elección: En sospecha de HID en pacientes estables.","guid":"cAEeFUtGCGYhxqICc45f3A","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"Características de la CE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"• Exploración del ID: Permite explorar generalmente todo el intestino delgado.","guid":"a-2yWXuAYJde349rAlvjWA","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"• Funcionamiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Cápsula deglutida.","guid":"Uq9fiRuFN4d9BVW4U2feQw","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"67","text":"• Recorrido pasivo gracias a la motilidad intestinal.","guid":"VPfGRGMQgjcOxMEiDhtBDw","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"67","text":"• Transmisión de múltiples fotos secuenciales (2-6 por segundo) a un aparato de grabación externo.","guid":"Sb_63i3zGpJGFL2mEqq1Ug","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"• Análisis de imágenes mediante software para identificar lesiones con alta precisión.","guid":"A41BxwZU-QpB84l9UniZ4w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"63","text":"• Ventajas:","guid":"RVvx0UIOA4MFMUrADxvsrw","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Estudio no invasivo y seguro.","guid":"ZhfBTWxIKRlV23tGHRU7GA","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Ubicación aproximada de las lesiones según tiempo transcurrido del examen y porcentaje del ID recorrido.","guid":"FMQUjVpNeJILMuZOFG8RIw","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• Alto rendimiento diagnóstico, aunque variable (40%-90% de los casos).","guid":"dvyEMRGxo_0nuXx6Yuo2ig","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"• Alta tasa de estudio completo del ID (80%-90%).","guid":"DTIElAaZC-ZlRhniX-FkHQ","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"72","text":"• Alto valor predictivo negativo (80%-100%).","guid":"Ih5DbWJLb5ozSUJhdxYJsQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"63","text":"• Rendimiento\\Ndiagnóstico:","guid":"UZsBcGO6K39GBvnAN7LCvQ","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"• General: 59,4% según metaanálisis (Liao, 2010).","guid":"UAJUmBvidQZUx_3VZMZpJQ","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"• Lesiones vasculares (angiodisplasia): Etiología más frecuente (50%).","guid":"di_tmF_65CR5NXpIbSxxyQ","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"78","text":"• Experiencia local chilena: Rendimiento similar (50-60%), con lesiones inflamatorias (46%) y vasculares (40%)\\Ncomo causas más frecuentes.","guid":"cayIISDu9sNQFqhTft6MtQ","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"78","text":"Factores que Mejoran el\\NRendimiento Diagnóstico","guid":"F6gx0BIJMzRAvE_HXQQjog","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"• Hemoglobina < 10 g/dL.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"82","text":"• Duración del sangrado > 6 meses.","guid":"VBc2t0XtmodsIBBRRBhUzA","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"82","text":"• Hemorragia recurrente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"82","text":"• Sangrado evidente versus oculto: 60% versus 46%.","guid":"ETOi7Q3mslM3prSoYs6kXg","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"82","text":"• Realización precoz: Dentro de las 2 semanas desde inicio del episodio (91% versus 34%),\\Nespecialmente dentro de las primeras 72 h de la sospecha de HID evidente.","guid":"caDd0n2trmgagWcbQaMyag","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"63","text":"Score Predictivo\\N(Mayra y cols.)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"• Pacientes hospitalizados.","guid":"T0RJFR-fFdh87ILQQPDRNg","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"• Mayores de 54 años.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"• Hemoglobina < 6,4 g/dL.","guid":"QI4Mm00DKyQ_z13raBYPRA","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"63","text":"Riesgos y\\NContraindicaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Retención de\\Nla cápsula:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"• Ocurre en 1%-2% de los casos.","guid":"Al_tWh6PTr4xvFVaGggfKg","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"• El lugar de la retención explica la causa de la HID en la mayoría de los casos (> 85%).","guid":"MJiB8nJ4pSF3DELMBK-4qQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"92","text":"• Mayor riesgo\\Nde retención:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"• Sospecha o confirmación de enfermedad de Crohn (5%-10%).","guid":"OGY_qGMsUx5IyA11SZnilg","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"• Sospecha de neoplasia.","guid":"cRMFcQBuwh4saIb0YrPjRA","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"• Antecedente de radiación abdominal.","guid":"fhxwhkbp7g8kVxWuF6yT9Q","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"96","text":"• Usuarios crónicos de AINEs.","guid":"NjNTAErAsT4nbKT8BXecFQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"92","text":"• Contraindicaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"• Obstrucción intestinal.","guid":"al_HFyRZJ8xGaG1LKu3Tsg","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"• Estenosis conocida.","guid":"cVxS8AY3yzcTA-L3c7xASg","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"38","text":"Enteroscopía Profunda Asistida con\\NDispositivos (EPAD)","guid":"JMcZ9UTAOFENxF91VV-b6A","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"Características\\Nde la EPAD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"• Procedimientos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"• Enteroscopía asistida por balón (simple o doble).","guid":"NzjdcwTQokFaD1SRb58dGw","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"• Enteroscopía espiral.","guid":"Z_z1XyLXYgc5OP-xWQ_60Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"105","text":"• Diagnóstico: Obtención de muestras.","guid":"LIt0tWAa88M5DyigYr7HtQ","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"105","text":"• Terapéutico: Marcación de lesiones para seguimiento endoscópico y cirugía.","guid":"KtulAmB7zZxoNmPLFTtsGQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"104","text":"Enteroscopía Doble\\NBalón (EDB)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"• Vías de Realización:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"113","parent":"112","text":"• Oral (anterógrada, más frecuente).","guid":"BNT1aS6e0RZAKT_LdjFIWQ","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"112","text":"• Anal (retrógrada).","guid":"NNacTVMtIsJp7YikWZ22Qw","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"112","text":"• A veces necesario realizar ambas (enteroscopía completa), idealmente en días separados.","guid":"F-1bFHex6Bku_VIrTyY4hw","children":[]}]},{"id":"116","parent":"111","text":"• Insuflación con CO2 recomendada para mayor profundidad de avance.","guid":"fIKKWgkMprw-xVWiZH9_ug","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"111","text":"• Alcance:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"118","parent":"117","text":"• Anterógrada: Desde el duodeno hasta el íleon proximal.","guid":"K-QIw3f-VVQ9j3qLTyos6A","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"117","text":"• Retrógrada: Íleon distal.","guid":"XZ_b-XlTWKBwjMGUCitQrg","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"117","text":"• Profundidad depende de resecciones previas y/o bridas que dificulten el avance.","guid":"WW5MYymb6jRs6hhkBEnxZQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"121","parent":"111","text":"• Generalmente requiere estudio bidireccional para enteroscopía completa.","guid":"Che30VUgfC8ZhV1-DuytOg","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"111","text":"• Rendimiento Diagnóstico:","guid":"A79NRVmunUoFHfWTOJXpkw","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"• Varía entre 40%-80%.","guid":"LNvADG8LfjcSM5_WRMkbIA","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"• Permite realizar hemostasia, dilatación por balón y resección de pólipos.","guid":"Zr1mUEEw8gET71OnYz_wqw","children":[]}]},{"id":"125","parent":"111","text":"• Tasa de\\NComplicaciones:","guid":"Sj2YvVK0qUpHv3BldiGhgQ","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"• Diagnóstica: 0,8%.","guid":"SrL-ngVO6vBFS85pKFLalw","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"• Terapéutica: 4%.","guid":"fqJDkDXYj_0yfitGWBCP8w","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"111","text":"• Principales complicaciones: Hemorragia,\\Nperforación, pancreatitis aguda.","guid":"X3R6Mh9oQ6pcWoFZaYwyAw","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"• Pancreatitis aguda en 0,3% de los casos, asociada a\\Nincremento de presión intraluminal duodenal y/o tracción.","guid":"dIi_2XXf3td4eN89eEgNHg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"104","text":"Recomendaciones\\Nen Caso de HID","guid":"","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"• Estudio de CE previa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"• Incrementa rendimiento diagnóstico.","guid":"T458IX2W1NAw3faxfGo8Lg","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"• Define mejor la vía de ingreso (anterógrada vs. retrógrada).","guid":"bKJTCEMRlodBM1dOU1-5WA","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"• Reduce riesgos de procedimiento invasivo (sedación profunda o anestesia general, duración promedio 2 h).","guid":"BEKIiFUiqvY2n6oDToAhRg","children":[]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"130","text":"• Indicaciones de\\NEPAD Inicial:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"• Hemorragia masiva.","guid":"J9dUQH5fGmhEocLHcopS3g","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"135","text":"• Contraindicaciones para CE.","guid":"A64FWAntkTAa3S11AlBI6A","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"135","text":"• Identificación de lesión probable mediante otro método de imagen.","guid":"P8YhLk1bWLtaYNjcHzqbYA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"38","text":"Enteroscopía de Empuje\\N(Push-enteroscopy)","guid":"bMOcZTa7WjUIxs1jYUxcPg","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"Indicaciones de Uso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"• Lesiones proximales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"• Sospecha de lesiones en duodeno o yeyuno proximal cercano al Treitz.","guid":"LJs5DAE_rKBZlGldfCm1Lg","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"• CE previa detecta lesiones en el primer 15% de su avance en el ID.","guid":"ftaBcApyYA54k_Fca3jUeA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"144","parent":"139","text":"Características de la\\NEnteroscopía de Empuje","guid":"","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"• Procedimiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"146","parent":"145","text":"• Realizada habitualmente mediante colonoscopio pediátrico.","guid":"TYP2ljnHSKo-2I3RUcZ_Hg","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"145","text":"• Permite explorar 50-120 cm del yeyuno proximal.","guid":"DunzoHV4N9QgRqBkNsFH4A","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"144","text":"• Rendimiento\\NDiagnóstico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"• Varía entre 24%-56% en casos de HID.","guid":"c9dSPWToYyspS5q-d4VXlQ","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"• Permite tomar muestras de tejido.","guid":"btX0XEQoyDR51aB-LpwVig","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"148","text":"• Tiene potencial terapéutico.","guid":"EYQg71Q2eVpN1rDqfke9VQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"144","text":"• Comparación\\Ncon EPAD:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"• Menor capacidad de avance y estabilidad para realizar terapéutica.","guid":"CvHTj1adfk1flBmTN40Mmw","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"152","text":"• Desarrollo de EPAD ha reducido su uso.","guid":"V90q7TkogvAztsHJVrOsXQ","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"152","text":"• Menor costo y mayor disponibilidad en muchos centros.","guid":"Q5ri_yxKsyVCLIDWER7ZlQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"156","parent":"139","text":"Ventajas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"157","parent":"156","text":"• Menor costo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"156","text":"• Mayor disponibilidad.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"139","text":"Desventajas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"• Menor capacidad de avance comparado con EPAD.","guid":"ZhH70AEFDqdi5VizdPvvcA","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"• Menor estabilidad para procedimientos terapéuticos.","guid":"dn1GewMr-RgrvTdRalSYuA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"38","text":"Estudios\\NRadiológicos","guid":"aBRcQ1UI0g9h2fBOVupQnw","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"Estudios Baritados","guid":"GTGaQ1uvkMwFhmYpKrW7Mw","children":[{"id":"164","parent":"163","text":"• Recomendación: No se recomienda su uso para estudiar la HID por su baja eficiencia.","guid":"KfqVYAiRkhtyZOpQAdfATQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"162","text":"Enterografía\\Npor TAC o RNM","guid":"L-YKJlNdFxMo_XiIOtfdtQ","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"• Evaluación: Permite evaluar la pared del intestino y órganos extradigestivos.","guid":"QboVDCYbrBpYi2yrBVT4Cw","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"• Riesgos: Mínimos, aunque la TAC implica irradiación.","guid":"UmZfPxq37YEWc9GgOHhbDw","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"• Limitaciones: Identificación de lesiones planas o pequeñas (angiodisplasias); no permite terapia.","guid":"G7z8KHlZKlMtdEqAEjpCow","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"165","text":"• Utilidad Principal:","guid":"LjpT4F5oy6o7g9BOR2vuJA","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"• CE no disponible, incompleta, negativa o contraindicada.","guid":"fIUja1kxgdF8jttcZJl_rw","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"• Debe preceder a la CE en EII establecida, historia de radioterapia, cirugía de ID (resección)\\No sospecha de lesiones estenóticas/obstructivas (tumores o enfermedad de Crohn).","guid":"OhhcdkEKNnhyIalXaf5mnA","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"165","text":"• Enterografía por TAC preferida en sospecha de HID; RNM en pacientes con contraindicaciones para TAC o jóvenes con EII o síndromes genéticos (Peutz-Jeghers).","guid":"FGdNixsfId8k1kRRPmHi7A","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"162","text":"Angiografía Abdomen-Pelvis por\\NTomografía Computada (Angio-TAC)","guid":"I7Cz-hc7LqFAOaM5ZWrJBg","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"• Descripción: Tomografía computada con fase de inyección de contraste arterial.","guid":"PVbauxjFD-Rqv8ERD705-w","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"• Detección: Sangrado activo mayor de 0,3-0,5 ml/min.","guid":"M3z9ZQEzkrFINZUKTzn5jQ","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"• Utilidad: Confirmar HID y ubicar la lesión; preferido en hemorragia digestiva aguda evidente y pacientes hemodinámicamente estables.","guid":"eoy9BXWp34phdDwxdxHgcA","children":[]}]},{"id":"177","parent":"162","text":"Cintigrafía con Tecnecio Marcado\\N(pertecnectato de Tc 99m)","guid":"TtthW14DF41bq2AffRW1PA","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"• Indicaciones: Sospecha de divertículo de Meckel sangrante.","guid":"PGvjNxcvMG5EgaNgdoQ_rQ","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"• Sensibilidad: 50%-90%.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"177","text":"• Recomendación: En pacientes jóvenes con HID activa evidente, con CE y enterografías normales.","guid":"WDlm5jajTLdggqZJbKC0cQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"162","text":"Angiografía","guid":"UcJulgVY6porApdddXMikA","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"• Detección: Hemorragia activa con flujo mayor de 0,5 ml/min.","guid":"HJQZO2s8Opda3euXWerz9w","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"• Rendimiento Diagnóstico: 27%-77%.","guid":"BAFKe0WdrKhpqC3yN35H4Q","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"181","text":"• Limitaciones: No suele identificar etiología, salvo en malformaciones vasculares grandes.","guid":"RtE_WjHdwvwGuEFuQV38Xw","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"181","text":"• Utilidad: Embolización selectiva del origen del sangrado.","guid":"J4eih2gsfZ84b9zPdmMD4g","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"181","text":"• Indicaciones: HID aguda evidente masiva, pacientes hemodinámicamente inestables.","guid":"Ri-VLBQbPO9zeLkeApt4Yw","children":[]}]},{"id":"187","parent":"162","text":"Enteroscopía\\NIntraoperatoria","guid":"K0ptXTf6XH55H7gQA4PUQw","children":[{"id":"188","parent":"187","text":"• Descripción: Método diagnóstico y terapéutico invasivo.","guid":"bp2pNVmiXllwJIi0QGAXyw","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"187","text":"• Indicación: Pacientes con HID y transfusiones/hospitalizaciones recurrentes sin etiología.","guid":"XvtI8xsnIBI10zpce49iLw","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"187","text":"• Preferencia: En casos escogidos, especialmente con cirugías previas y adherencias intestinales.","guid":"BmNaqRCxJfNVelYmCmSlJA","children":[]}]},{"id":"191","parent":"162","text":" Test de Sangre Oculta en\\NDeposiciones (TSOD)","guid":"Vk7Smz8ihBhB4u0FHSAR9Q","children":[{"id":"192","parent":"191","text":"• Descripción: Detecta pérdidas de 5-10 ml/día.","guid":"cQBHFEibLnRefg5UGIfpmw","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"191","text":"• Test Inmunoquímicos: Más útiles en sangrados bajos; detectan hemoglobina humana intacta.","guid":"MMesExbt6yQO6u1-dvdBQA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"194","parent":"0","text":"Manejo","guid":"KwkoEwJjppx5krmjVlOVcA","children":[{"id":"195","parent":"194","text":"Desafíos del Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"• Dificultades de acceso al intestino delgado (ID).","guid":"Ol4DG3KycbRZ12mzKPusUA","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"• Rendimiento diagnóstico condicionado por la presencia de sangrado activo.","guid":"TFTQDUn78mdpW8QcK1AZAQ","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"195","text":"• Posibilidad de múltiples estudios y hospitalizaciones, implicando altos costos y frustración.","guid":"ZSMSeR8u_ngm33swa4ZtIg","children":[]}]},{"id":"199","parent":"194","text":"Estrategias de Manejo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"200","parent":"199","text":"1. Presentación Clínica:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"• Oculta vs. Evidente.","guid":"L-Aka3xZ0VZ16xJHBi73Bg","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"200","text":"• Estado Hemodinámico:","guid":"O3xVbjfN_0wjTwj8LHycgg","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"• Estable.","guid":"AGktwAHNF1BFBIYeMTDZ1A","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"• Inestable.","guid":"GLsCdFPvc5woKBsUQ8Qqhw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"205","parent":"199","text":"2. Métodos Diagnósticos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"• Utilización inteligente según la presentación clínica y recursos disponibles.","guid":"VlMaOCG61LcaF7_3ELEdUw","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"• Involucrar un equipo multidisciplinario (gastroenterólogo, cirujano, endoscopista, radiólogo).","guid":"FG1Ga3PvKao5rMmkYMIWeQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"199","text":"3. Tratamiento Inicial:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"• Cápsula\\NEndoscópica (CE):","guid":"PescEiMIjcAMEi96Iw4uiw","children":[{"id":"210","parent":"209","text":"• Estudio inicial de elección.","guid":"QjeMODLxqqoOlJuuchewow","children":[]},{"id":"211","parent":"209","text":"• Definir el mejor tratamiento definitivo.","guid":"L0t8AAR_rfV4RqepasfRbg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"199","text":"4. Opciones de\\NTratamiento Definitivo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"• Endoscópico:","guid":"PE2tQRuVsKUXRG3wPLbbAg","children":[{"id":"214","parent":"213","text":"• Hemostasia endoscópica.","guid":"HWLH9lxI9A5t57TWNh3Kag","children":[]}]},{"id":"215","parent":"212","text":"• Quirúrgico:","guid":"MDhnqhYPz-p54fTyBouB4w","children":[{"id":"216","parent":"215","text":"• Resección de lesiones.","guid":"N8qkoRP5tOkXPJ82TDfrDQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"217","parent":"212","text":"• Seguimiento Clínico:","guid":"B-jelFDpaNos-gGGRdP6pg","children":[{"id":"218","parent":"217","text":"• Suplementación de hierro y/o hemoderivados.","guid":"c_H2mjkMMQBo4ikxNimC0g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"219","parent":"199","text":"5. Tratamientos\\NEspeciales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"• Angiodisplasias Múltiples, Recurrentes y Refractarias:","guid":"a_3bqnd2xN8oQTN1G0lXqg","children":[{"id":"221","parent":"220","text":"• Medicamentos vasoactivos o antiangiogénicos (estrógenos, octreotide o talidomida).","guid":"e_Zy1CCH2x8GESkYOEQgFg","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"222","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"PB2LxB1Vlwh0-vsYWYBTug","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"Factores que Afectan\\Nel Pronóstico","guid":"eZ6LF2Lir-4Pnh4lKdbywQ","children":[{"id":"224","parent":"223","text":"1. Patología de Base:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"• Lesiones Vasculares del ID:","guid":"ePJ_2AmAExcwYnSkML0keQ","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"• Recurrencia >30% al año.","guid":"HXnIAEefE9t89Q-GJWKmlA","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"225","text":"• Predictores: Enfermedad cardíaca, hemorragia evidente al momento de presentación.","guid":"GIh8tSnvEQxrNqE6DHpzUA","children":[]}]},{"id":"228","parent":"224","text":"• Tumores:","guid":"YvtCDFQYymxCo_YiTvkdtg","children":[{"id":"229","parent":"228","text":"• Pronóstico depende de si son benignos o malignos.","guid":"S4-PS2rlKZhqQnVgR4YCIA","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"• Considerar síndromes genéticos (poliposis familiar) que requieren seguimiento a largo plazo y tratamientos repetidos.","guid":"C20Et3BTnnh_yiI2R4qQew","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"231","parent":"224","text":"• Enteropatía por AINEs:","guid":"Dak1gXTFHU4hCuQ2B0fAmA","children":[{"id":"232","parent":"231","text":"• Muy buen pronóstico al suspender su uso.","guid":"V6fNPDCpAlsxHrNZUJpNFA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"233","parent":"223","text":"2. Evaluación\\NPost-Tratamiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"• Cápsula Endoscópica (CE) Negativa:","guid":"OikVcmGBJ_4BV3GNV6Ldcg","children":[{"id":"235","parent":"234","text":"• Bajo riesgo de resangrado (5%-25%).","guid":"KSA72X5MgRR9BYQHQai4jg","children":[]}]},{"id":"236","parent":"233","text":"• Similar entre HID oculta y evidente.","guid":"KDuSIGg8JUFOIyveCzbULQ","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"233","text":"• Estrategia de manejo: Observar y esperar.","guid":"PFTvrRDHIgFaL_HjB-R--Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"222","text":"Factores de Riesgo\\Nde Resangrado","guid":"","children":[{"id":"239","parent":"238","text":"1. Cambio de presentación clínica (de oculto a evidente).","guid":"e6xLmURyZ0RPaoEZBxlQUA","children":[]},{"id":"240","parent":"238","text":"2. Anemización mayor a 4 g/dl.","guid":"NMYFvE80o09Oo-DLQm87PQ","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"238","text":"3. Necesidad de transfusión de >5 unidades de glóbulos rojos.","guid":"Q_nAnW-uxQFJtvvVG6GN2Q","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"238","text":"4. Usuarios de anticoagulantes.","guid":"IFfHXHrVry9sO9rtWoDczg","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"238","text":"5. Edad avanzada.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"244","parent":"222","text":"Reevaluación y\\NSeguimiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"245","parent":"244","text":"• Pacientes con Resangrado\\Ndespués de 2 años:","guid":"XFbXLW2TTHoyI7pBBXcTBg","children":[{"id":"246","parent":"245","text":"• Considerar estudio adicional para\\Ndescartar una etiología diferente.","guid":"a9_Nji8pPkhHH8uUFBtfrw","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":246,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Gastroenterología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Gastroenterología","filename":"- Hemorragia del Intestino Delgado-2024","id":"map_638","resolved_references":[]}